parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electric seatbelt retractor can cause the seatbelt to become stuck in the forward position, leading to a lack of proper restraint, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt retractor fails to operate
the seatbelt becomes stuck in the forward position
the red seatbelt light is on
a constant beeping sound is heard
the seatbelt retractor makes no sound when failing
the seatbelt only loosens when the door is re-opened.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The over-retraction of the automatic seatbelt can cause the belt to become stuck, leading to a lack of proper restraint, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt over-retracts as the passenger door is closed and the seat is occupied
the belt only loosens when the door is re-opened.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The seatbelt unlatching can cause the belt to become unsecured, leading to a lack of proper restraint, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelt unlatches as if the door had been opened
the belt becomes unsecured when going over a bump or hitting a ditch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS pump can cause the anti-lock brake system to malfunction, leading to brake lock-up or loss of braking ability, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS pump runs continuously
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the vehicle experiences brake lock-up
unusual noises or vibrations when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to feel soft or spongy, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
loose hydraulic pressure when stopping
must pump pedal to stop and keep the car from rolling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS sensor or electronic system can cause the anti-lock brake system to malfunction, leading to brake lock-up or loss of braking ability, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS system activates under normal braking
unusual noises or vibrations when braking
the vehicle occasionally stops when going over small bumps.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck brake caliper can cause uneven brake wear, reduced braking ability, and increased stopping distances, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking
uneven brake wear
unusual noises or vibrations when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails completely
the vehicle is unable to move
harsh noise when shifting into reverse
loose bolt inside the transmission causing a hole in the transmission case.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Differential unit failure can cause loss of power to the wheels, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The differential unit fails due to pin breaking
causing loss of power to the wheels.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failure can cause inconvenience and distraction to the driver, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Problems with interior lights
cassette player
and door locks
leaks from one of the windows
rust on the outside door and bottom of the door.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Disputes over TSBs can lead to confusion and frustration for vehicle owners, potentially delaying necessary repairs.
symptoms: Acura claims the TSB is only a mechanic's guideline and does not indicate a defect
despite the TSB citing a defect code (NO.042) and symptoms matching the owner's experience.
